REST stands for Representational State Transfer.
It is a way to implement communication between two apps.
It's client-server communication model, stateless communication.
It is idely used for building scalale and easy to maintain APIs.

HTTP Methods

1. Get : Retrieve data from the server(read).
2. POST : Send data to the server to create a new resources.
3. PUT : Update an existing resource with new data.
4. DELETE : Remove a resource from the server.
5. PATCH : Partially update an existing resources.

